cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with image processing and analysis, specifically the creation of dictionaries using NMF applied to reordered pixels of single images. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses NMF as a low-rank approximation technique and evaluates the algorithm using PSNR and MSSIM, which are commonly used in machine learning. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the efficient storage of large datasets through the creation of low-rank approximations. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper uses numerical techniques such as SVD and NMF for low-rank approximations and dictionary creation.
